reviews.review_text:
Holy smoke! There are, of course, a bazillion Scarlet->Fires that a great, but I gotta tip my beanie to  one more--this one. This is definitely a new fav, due, partially, to the wicked transition.

I'll add that I've not yet compared this copy to others, but it sounds great to me. Thanks to Alla who contributed, and--Nice work, Dave.

This is a fun show... ...and it sounds great to boot!

I've never heard them have the kind of fun they seem to be having in Fire and Dancin' particularly.  Just lots of weird vocal stuff, yelling, moaning and other stuff.  Maybe it was common, I am no expert.

Great sounding show...Bobby comes in early on Dancin, just like 5/8 the year before :-)

Thanks to all involved in bringing this sweetness to my ears.

Scah-Lit/Fie-Ya! Up there in central New England they love them some Scah-Lit/Fie-Ya....Scarlet/Fire to the rest of us!  78 was the Dead's disco year but this show hasn't a trace.  It's Rock & Roll Grateful Dead style with some New England flavor thrown into the mix, making this an incredible show and extremely solid recording.  You can crank this one to eleven no problem provided you have no neighbors!
